  "prompt": "How should I fill my first name and last name in a form, when I have my surname as first name in India?",
  "response": "In many Western contexts, forms typically ask for the first name followed by the last name, reflecting the \"given name\" and \"surname\" order. However, in many Indian naming conventions, the surname is often mentioned first, especially in informal or traditional contexts. Here\u2019s how you can fill out a form depending on the situation:\n\n1. **Follow the Instructions on the Form:** If the form specifies \"First Name\" and \"Last Name,\" you can follow these instructions:\n   - \"First Name\" (Given Name): Enter what is traditionally your given name.\n   - \"Last Name\" (Surname): Enter your surname.\n\n2. **Consistency with Official Documents:** Always ensure that the way you fill in your name is consistent with your legal documents (passport, driver's license), as this will be crucial for identification and verification. \n\n3. **Full Name Box:** If there is a single box for \"Full Name,\" enter your name in the order that is consistent with official documentation.\n\n4. **Provide Clarification if Necessary:** If there is any note section or opportunity to add comments, you can clarify that your surname is being used as your first name for consistency.\n\n5. **Contact Information or Help Desk:** If unsure, consider contacting the provider of the form for guidance.\n\nBy following these steps, you can avoid confusion and ensure your name is recorded correctly.",
